blog.name: inikavulpixelreviews
blog.title: Let's Talk About Pokemon!
blog.description:
Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Rufflet and Braviary
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Rufflet and Braviary
body:
627: Rufflet

Hahahahaha. Look at this little floofster. Rufflet is as cute and ridiculous looking as you’d expect a clear cut baby bird Pokemon to look. Can’t help but appreciate it for that much if nothing else.

Personal Score: 7.5/10

Adorable.

628: Braviary

Yeah, I’m sure everyone saw this one coming from a million miles away. Just like how the French region’s gotta have its poodle, and the Hawaiian region’s gotta have a lei, here’s the United States region to bring us Braviary, the unashamed American eagle. Complete with red, white, and blue color scheme. It’s a cool design and all, and I will be giving it a plenty passable score at the end of the day but. It’s just a disappointment that it’s a Pokemon here solely for iconography’s sake. Not that much special is done with it. It’s cool to have the fantasy realized, but it’s really predictable and nothing is really done to set it apart from any other bird Pokemon.

It’s just as predictable as say, if we get a region set in Canada and they bring us a Moose Pokemon that’s… just a moose. Yeah, it’s cool that we finally got a long-time bucket list Pokemon out of the way,  but it’s still an animal you just squandered the potential of.

Personal Score: 7.5/10

I like it despite it being pretty generic. But it could’ve been pretty high up there if it were a more fully realized idea.
